narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: You learn extensively about molecular experimental techniques (i.e. microscopy, sea urchin fertilization). You also learn how to distill complex scientific topics into 5-minute "chalk-talks."

I learned the most, practically, than I ever did in a course at Yale. This course was excellent at tackling the most basic experimental cell biology techniques, and by the end of it, you could read almost any research paper and understand exactly what was happening in their experimental methods.
You learn so so much in this course! It's exciting and engaging and we cover so much material both in theory and practice.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I think a little more structure and guidance on what determines your grade or what experiments you are even doing would be good.
Dr. Wolenski is such a gem. His care for his students and the course material really shines through in this class. It was a pleasure to be participating in such great experiments!

Professor Wolenski himself is this course's biggest strength. He displays a kind of commitment to the course, his students, and their learning that I think is very rare to find amongst other professors. Despite the long hours, this class feels like you're spending time with some of your favorite people for 10 hours every week. I appreciated the seminars Dr. Wolenski took us to at least once a week. It was always valuable seeing cutting edge research being done in a vast variety of subfields within cell biology, and our time there was almost always informed by what we learned in class.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes to complete your MCDB lab requirement as it fulfills the whole requirement in one semester and is a very chill lab.
Absolutely! You become very close to the other people in your lab class.

Yes, especially if you're not too comfortable with cell bio research and want to be. This class is such a perfect introduction and teaches you so much more. Professor Wolenski is one of those professors that you need to experience at least once in your life. The community this class becomes is so valuable and like Dr. Wolenski says, become a "family".
Yes! Take it if you are passionate about learning
